UNIVERSITY of Dar es Salaam (UDSM) Vice Chancellor, Prof. William Anangisye has called for reliable social and scientific research among higher learning institution as part of their responsibility towards providing solutions in the community. With the world troubleshooting a pile of unreliable research papers among university libraries, the academic don says, researches are key for the university survival and its contribution in the country. “Without researches, higher learning institutions are likely to be at high risk of replicating secondary school education qualities,” he said at the sixth research and innovation work being held in Dar es Salaam.